---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Insurance Software Delivery" description="Predictable software delivery for insurance carriers, MGAs, and brokerages. State filing deadlines, carrier platforms, and claims systems — delivered on forecast." fullWidth>

  <div class="hero-dark hero-centered">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Insurance</span>
      <h1>Software delivery that meets<br><em>regulatory deadlines</em></h1>
      <p class="hero-subtext">State filing dates don't move. Carrier requirements don't negotiate. Your software delivery partner needs to operate with the same precision your regulators demand.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="ind-challenges">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <h2 class="section-heading">The problem with insurance software</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Insurance technology has unique constraints that most development teams aren't built for.</p>

      <div class="steps-grid">
        <div class="step-cell">
          <h3>State Filing Deadlines</h3>
          <p>Every state has its own filing requirements and timelines. Miss a deadline and you delay market entry by months. Your development timeline has to align with regulatory calendars, not sprint cycles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-cell">
          <h3>Carrier &amp; MGA Platforms</h3>
          <p>Building a carrier or MGA platform means integrating with rating engines, policy admin systems, and distribution networks — all with their own technical requirements and certification processes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-cell">
          <h3>Regulatory Scrutiny</h3>
          <p>Every feature that touches underwriting, pricing, or claims handling operates under regulatory oversight. Compliance isn't a phase — it's a constraint on every delivery.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-cell">
          <h3>Claims Systems</h3>
          <p>Claims processing has to work on day one. Policyholders filing claims don't care about your deployment schedule. The system is either ready or it isn't.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="ind-solution">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Predictive Delivery</span>
      <h2>How we solve it</h2>
      <p>Predictive delivery was built for environments where deadlines are non-negotiable and the cost of being wrong is measured in regulatory delays, not just budget overruns.</p>
      <ul class="ind-solution-list">
        <li><strong>Forecasted timelines, not estimates.</strong> NolteOS uses historical delivery data to forecast when each piece of work will ship. You know before you commit whether your regulatory deadline is achievable.</li>
        <li><strong>Fixed price per delivery.</strong> Every delivery has a clear definition of done, acceptance criteria, and a fixed price. No scope creep, no surprise invoices when compliance requirements surface mid-build.</li>
        <li><strong>Compliance built into every cycle.</strong> We don't bolt compliance on at the end. Every delivery cycle accounts for regulatory constraints, documentation requirements, and audit trail needs.</li>
        <li><strong>Transparent progress.</strong> Real-time delivery metrics in NolteOS mean you always know where you stand relative to your filing deadlines — not after a status meeting, but right now.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="case-studies">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Proven in production</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Real insurance software, delivered predictably.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="case-grid ind-case-single">
      <div class="case-card">
        <div class="case-card-top">
          <span class="case-card-logo-text">Odie</span>
          <div class="case-card-metrics">
            <span class="case-metric">120 <span class="case-metric-label">deliveries</span></span>
            <span class="case-metric">95% <span class="case-metric-label">accuracy</span></span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="case-card-body">
          <div class="case-card-meta-line">
            <span class="case-pill">Insurance</span>
            <span class="case-stage">Series A — Pet Insurance MGA</span>
          </div>
          <h3>Odie</h3>
          <p class="case-desc">Insurance platform built from zero under carrier requirements and state regulatory obligations. Thousands of active policyholders across multiple states.</p>
          <div class="case-meta">
            <div class="case-meta-item"><span class="case-meta-value">3 years</span><span class="case-meta-label">Partnership</span></div>
            <div class="case-meta-item"><span class="case-meta-value">120</span><span class="case-meta-label">Deliveries</span></div>
            <div class="case-meta-item"><span class="case-meta-value">95%</span><span class="case-meta-label">Accuracy</span></div>
            <div class="case-meta-item"><span class="case-meta-value">State Reg</span><span class="case-meta-label">Compliance</span></div>
          </div>
          <a class="case-link" href="/work/odie">Read the full case study &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="predictability-cta">
    <div class="predictability-cta-inner">
      <div class="predictability-cta-content">
        <div class="os-tag">NolteOS <span class="live-dot"></span></div>
        <h2>See what predictable insurance delivery looks like.</h2>
        <p>Describe what you're building. NolteOS forecasts the scope, timeline, and cost — before you commit a single line of code.</p>
        <a class="btn-accent" href="https://os.nolte.io">See Your Forecast</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</Base>

<style>
  .ind-challenges {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--white);
  }
  .ind-solution {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--gray-100);
  }
  .ind-solution h2 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
  }
  .ind-solution p {
    max-width: 640px;
    color: var(--gray-600);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .ind-solution-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 2rem 0 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 640px;
  }
  .ind-solution-list li {
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--gray-600);
  }
  .ind-solution-list strong {
    color: var(--black);
  }
  .ind-case-single {
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .case-studies {
    padding: 5rem 0;
  }
</style>
